Basic Linux Commands

1. pwd -> print current working directory
	/ -> root	bin -> binaries
	
2. ls	->	list all the files and directories inside work dir

Inside the bin directory
	bin -> binaries
	home -> user directory (~) -> tilde
	cd ~	->	Any dir to home directly
	
	admin user == super user == root user
	sudo	->	for admin access
	whoami	->	current user
	
	ls -l	->	directories in listed way
total 12
drwxr-xr-x  2 root              root              4096 Sep 26 10:46 abc
drwxr-xr-x 15 itilite           itilite           4096 Sep 13 17:05 itilite
drwxr-xr-x 19 saihiteshgorantla saihiteshgorantla 4096 Sep 26 10:37 saihiteshgorantla

	first character d -> it's an directory
	if it is hyphen(-) -> files
	rwx	->	read write and execute
	
	
	

	

	

	
